-- Meningitis Outbreak Rises to 285 Cases, U.S. CDC Says
-- B y   J o e   S a b o
-- 2012-10-21T18:30:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-21/meningitis-outbreak-rises-to-285-cases-u-s-cdc-says.html
One more person in the U.S. has
become ill in a fungal meningitis outbreak linked to tainted
steroid injections for back pain, while the death toll held at
23, health authorities said.  The contaminated drugs are tied to 285 reported illnesses
in 16 states, the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and
Prevention said today in an update posted on its website.
Included in the cases are three peripheral joint infections.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
